The seventh edition ,conducted from 8-10th September 2017, went on to become the largest with an outstanding delegate count of 337.The quality of the executive board was incomparable and increased participation from the delegates just added to it. Two international delegations made their way to the conference from Afghanistan, Bangladesh. In line with the theme , "Diplomacy and Beyond" , we conducted two SRD events and the Young Leaders Program. The first SRD event was organized at Devarakonda Basti School where the volunteers conducted a drawing competition and interacted with the kids there . The second event was at Tara Boys home where a mini library was established and was by far the largest event conducted under the SRD. Adip Krishna Guduru was given a chance to sit on the executive board of the African Union under the Young Leaders Program. He did exceedingly well gaining appreciation from the delegates as well as the organizers. Thus , with it's seventh edition , CBITMUN continued to rewrite history by growing bigger and better.

So here it is. That one final week of prep, that one final week of telling mum(a rather disappointed one) during dinner time, I will be just be there in 5 but actually you arrive at least half an hour later. That one final week of bunking because you worried that somebody is backing out or things aren't getting done. That one final week where you can legit scold your Secretariat to your heart's content. Reel it all in, guys. Reel each and every moment of it. Months of hard work and sacrifices. All those days of endlessly sitting down and figuring out a plan. Want to know a secret? (something which you would have already figured out). There is no such thing as a plan, even when you plan there will be hiccups. There will be that, "Oh fuck I(we) completely forgot" or like "Oh shit I(we) screwed up."
